text: I hold myself to very high standards.
I notice when things could be improved and feel responsible to help.
I feel uneasy when rules or processes are ignored.
I double-check details to avoid mistakes.
I can be critical of myself when I fall short.
I’m comfortable leaving things imperfect if the big picture is fine.
I’m quick to offer help when I see a need.
It’s hard for me to say no when someone asks for support.
I sense others’ feelings and adjust to comfort them.
I feel appreciated when my contributions are noticed.
I often prioritize my needs over others’ needs.
I worry that if I don’t help, I won’t be valued.
I’m motivated by goals and visible results.
I adapt my presentation to fit the audience and succeed.
Recognition for performance energizes me.
I track metrics or outcomes to gauge success.
I’m comfortable failing publicly if it serves learning.
I sometimes compare myself to others to measure progress.
I value being authentic, even if it sets me apart.
I look for depth and emotional meaning in experiences.
I can feel misunderstood or different from others.
I prefer unique approaches over conventional ones.
I easily detach from strong feelings and keep things simple.
I’m comfortable sharing complex emotions with others.
I like to fully understand systems before acting.
I need time and space to process information.
I conserve my energy and resources deliberately.
I prefer analysis and data over speculation.
I jump into action quickly without much research.
I’m fine being interrupted frequently while working.
I plan for risks and possible problems.
Reliability and commitment are very important to me.
I scan for what could go wrong to prepare in advance.
Clear expectations and guardrails help me do my best work.
I’m comfortable moving ahead with ambiguity and minimal safeguards.
I often seek reassurance before making a big decision.
I enjoy new ideas, options, and experiences.
I reframe setbacks quickly and stay future-focused.
I prefer flexibility over rigid plans.
I like to keep the mood upbeat and moving.
I’m content staying with one option even if it feels limiting.
I avoid uncomfortable feelings by switching to something more fun.
I naturally take charge when things need doing.
I speak directly and value strength and honesty.
I protect my team and challenge obstacles.
I push for decisive action when stalled.
I’m fine letting others lead, even if the direction seems weak.
I soften my approach to avoid intimidating others.
I avoid unnecessary conflict when possible.
I’m good at seeing multiple perspectives.
I go with the flow and support consensus.
I value a calm, steady environment.
I assert my own priorities even if it creates tension.
I sometimes minimize my needs to keep the peace.
